Steps of Algorithmic Thinking 

    1. Identify and define the problem clearly to determine how to proceed.
    2. Inpuit all the information you already know.
    3. Break down all your task into smaller chunks.
    4. Organize steps into the most logical order.
    5. Anticipate Variables using the if if-then approach.
    6. Define your steps around the variables you might encounter.
    7. Plan a loop in oyur algorithm if you do not solve the problem at first.
    8. Adjust your aproach if you encounter unexpected variables.
    